snippet.title: Jaanam | Bad Newz | Vicky Kaushal | Triptii Dimri | Vishal Mishra | In cinemas 19th July
snippet.description:
After the first song 'Tauba Tauba' from the film Bad Newz now experience the magic of love with "Jaanam," where the charismatic Vicky Kaushal and Triptii Dimri set the screen on fire with their breathtaking chemistry. This romantic song sung by Vishal Mishra is a perfect blend of heartfelt emotions and visual splendor, making it a must-watch for all music lovers.

üëâ Subscribe to Saregama Music: https://bit.ly/3FkAS0W

Credits:
Composer : Vishal Mishra
Singer : Vishal Mishra
Lyrics : Vishal Mishra
All Music Produced Arranged & Designed By : Vishal Mishra
Music Assistants : Kumar Gaurav Singh & Trihangku Lahkar
Additional Female Vocals - Shreya Jain
Music Supervisor : Azeem Dayani
Associate Music Supervisor : Manish Natekar
Mixed and Mastered by : Eric Pillai @ Future Sound of Bombay
Recording Engineer @VM Studio : Trihangku Lahkar
Choreographer : Remo D‚Äôsouza

Bad Newz in cinemas 19th July.

Amazon Prime presents
In association with Dharma Productions and Leo Media Collective
A Leo Media Collective production
BAD NEWZ
Starring Vicky Kaushal, Triptii Dimri and Ammy Virk
Directed by Anand Tiwari
Produced by Hiroo Yash Johar, Karan Johar, Apoorva Mehta, Amritpal Singh Bindra & Anand
Tiwari
Written by Ishita Moitra & Tarun Dudeja

Lyrics:
Naina banjaron mein
Mushkilen aa baithi hain
Ishq bechaini ki
Ye talab la baithi hain

Aise na yun dekho dekho jaanam
Aise na yun dekho jaanam
Hona jayein hum bhi tere jaanam
Aise na yun dekho jaanam

Oo..

Hmm...
Kabhi aankhon se ye bayaan kare meri aadatein
Dil hai mera ab bezubaan teri raah take
Jaise humdum mile
Kaise hardum mile
Itni haseen ho phir
Ye saadgi hai kaise

Aasma mera hai
Dil jo ye tera hai
Ud raha main hadein tode

Dil pe aye janeja
Dhun teri aa baithi hai
Oo
Ishq bechaini ki
Ye talab la baithi hai

Aise na yun dekho dekho jaanam
Aise na yun dekho jaanam
Hona jaaye hum bhi tere jaanam
Aise na yun dekho jaanam

Oo

Ishq hade tere naam kare
Aur saans saans tere naam kare
Humdum mere humdum mere janaam
Mere janaam
Ishq hade tere naam kare
Aur saans saans iljaam kare
Humdum mere humdum mere jaanam

Ye talab la bethi hai
Ye talab la bethi hai
Ishq bechaini ki ye
Zindagi ka bethi hai
Dekho dekho jaanam
Aise na yun dekho jaanam

Join us on this special episode of #joshtalksmalayalam , as we pay tribute to the remarkable life of Anagha, a young girl who fought bravely against cancer. Despite her untimely passing, her legacy lives on through the inspiring journey she shared with us.

In this emotional and uplifting talk, Anagha's mother, Prameela, shares the remarkable story of her daughter's journey from being a teacher's daughter to becoming a cancer warrior. Despite facing numerous challenges, Anagha never lost hope and continued to inspire those around her with her courage and positivity.

Tragically, #anagha was unable to fulffulfilill her dream of speaking at Josh Talks Malayalam herself, but we are honoured to have Prameela share her daughter's story and fulfil Anagha's dream. This talk is a testament to the power of resilience, hope, and the human spirit.

As we remember Anagha's life and legacy, we are reminded that even in the darkest times, there is always something to be learned and shared with the world. This talk is not just a tribute to Anagha's life but also a celebration of her spirit and a reminder to all of us to live life to the fullest.

Please join us as we celebrate Anagha's inspiring journey and continue to spread her message of #hope and #positivity .

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbour. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Raj Anankat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises.

Nosherwan Ghaznavi, a wealthy young man, faces a pivotal moment in his life after his brother's death.
